    "value": "The identical Pleiades 1A and Pleiades 1B satellites deliver 50cm very high-resolution multispectral imagery with a 20km swath. They are operated on the same orbit as the SPOT 6 satellite, forming a 3-satellite constellation that enables intraday revisit to any point on Earth. The system offers five collection scenarios: target, strip mapping, tri-stereo, corridor and persistent monitoring, and serves both civil and military projects.",
